  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aims of this three-year study are to:

        1. explore the change of fatigue, nutritional status, quality of life and care needs in
           patients with operable pancreatic cancer perioperatively and following surgery within 3
           months.

        2. develop and evaluate the effect of patient-centered cancer prehabilitation care program
           on improving fatigue, nutritional status and quality of life (QOL) in this population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Develop and evaluate the effect of patient-centered cancer prehabilitation care program on
      improving fatigue, nutritional status and quality of life (QOL) in this population.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
